name: .VMF_AUTOSAVE File Extension
summary: Learn about .VMF_AUTOSAVE files and view a list of programs that open them.

description: Auto-generated file created by Hammer Editor, a program used to build maps for Valve games such as Half-Life; stores an autosaved, backup copy of the currently opened .VMF file.

content: VMF_AUTOSAVE files are used for recovering map data in the event the VMF file becomes corrupted, or if the program unexpectedly crashes.
